-- Greece May Grant Concessions for Country’s Ports, Imerisia Says
-- B y   T o m   S t o u k a s
-- 2012-07-02T07:37:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-02/greece-may-grant-concessions-for-country-s-ports-imerisia-says.html
Greece  will propose granting
concessions to run state-controlled ports instead of selling
stakes,  Imerisia  reported, without citing anyone.  Shipping Minister Konstantinos Mousouroulis will discuss
the proposal this week with Horst Reichenbach, the European
Union official helping to overhaul the country’s administration,
the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Tom Stoukas in Athens at 
 astoukas@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
